James Adrian CORNELIUS and Nora Irene Cornelius, v. The PRUDENTIAL INSURANCE COMPANY. No. 8055. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Feb. 14, 1939. D. A. Sachs, Jr., of Louisville, Ky., and Franklin Rives, of Hopkinsville, Ky., for appellants. H. W. Linton, of Hopkinsville, Ky., for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon application of the appellant, the appellee not objecting, it is now ordered that this cause be and the same is dismissed • — settled.
